  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Is this strictly true any more?\r\n\r\n> The hash of the EVM code of this account---this is the code that gets executed should this address receive a message call; it is \r\n> immutable and thus, unlike all other fields, cannot be changed after construction\r\n\r\n\"cannot be changed after construction\" - unless the contract is destroyed and re-initialized with CREATE2\r\n\r\nThere are so many potential security issues associated with assuming the contract code associated with an account is _actually_ immutable that I believe it is unwise to leave this as it stands. Should the second clause be deleted?",
